==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blain
<hw>Blain</hw> <pr>(bl⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>blein</ets>, <ets>bleyn</ets>, AS. <ets>bl⟦emac⟧gen</ets>; akin to
Dan. <ets>blegn</ets>, D. <ets>blein</ets>; perh. fr. the same root as
E. <ets>bladder</ets>. See <er>Bladder</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
inflammatory swelling or sore; a bulla, pustule, or blister.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Blotches and <qex>blains</qex> must all his flesh emboss.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A bladder growing on the root of
the tongue of a horse, against the windpipe, and stopping the
breath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blamable</ent>⟦br⟧
